# Image Gallery Patterns

## Gallery Item Structure

Every gallery item follows a consistent pattern: a container with an image, a hover-reveal save button, and a dropdown for board selection.

```html
<div class="gallery-item">
  <img src="..." alt="..." loading="lazy">
  <button class="gallery-save-btn">
    Save
    <div class="gallery-save-dropdown">
      <button class="gallery-save-dropdown-item">Inspiration</button>
      <button class="gallery-save-dropdown-item">References</button>
      <button class="gallery-save-dropdown-item">Favorites</button>
    </div>
  </button>
</div>
```

- Save button is **hidden by default** (`opacity: 0`) and revealed on `.gallery-item:hover`
- Dropdown appears on `.gallery-save-btn:hover` via `opacity`/`visibility`/`transform` transitions
- Board names: **Inspiration**, **References**, **Favorites**

## Grid Layouts

Use CSS Grid with `auto-fill` and `minmax` for responsive columns:

```css
/* Feed grid (home_logada) */
.feed-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr));
  gap: 16px;
}

/* Grid view (index) */
.grid-view-content {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr));
  gap: 12px;
  max-width: 1800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

Multiple layout presets use numbered classes (`layout-1` through `layout-4`) with `nth-child` rules for featured items spanning multiple columns/rows.

## Image Detail View

Full-screen overlay with two-panel layout: image area + sidebar.

```css
.image-detail {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 200;
  background: #000;
  display: flex;
}
```

- **Left panel** (`.detail-image-area`): centered image with prev/next navigation arrows and image counter
- **Right panel** (`.detail-sidebar`, 320px): color palette, description, tags, save button, "also saved by" users
- Toggle with `.active` class using `opacity`/`visibility` transitions
- Close button: pill-shaped with glass effect, positioned top-left at `z-index: 210`

## Save-to-Board Interactions

Two mechanisms for saving images:

1. **Dropdown save** — hover-reveal dropdown on gallery/grid items with board options
2. **Drag-to-board** — full-screen overlay (`.drag-boards-overlay`) with board targets, activated by dragging an image from the detail view

```css
/* Drag board target */
.drag-board-target {
  width: 160px;
  height: 100px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  border-radius: 8px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
}
```

## Glass Morphism Style for UI Controls

All interactive overlays use consistent glass styling:

```css
background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);     /* or rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9) for dropdowns */
backdrop-filter: blur(8px);           /* 8px for buttons, 12px for dropdowns */
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1–0.15);
border-radius: 4–6px;
```

## Hover Behavior

- Gallery items: save button fades in (`opacity: 0` → `1`)
- Feed items: lift effect (`translateY(-4px)`) + gradient overlay fades in
- Color swatches: `scale(1.2)` with hex tooltip
- All transitions use `0.2s ease` or `var(--transition)` (`0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`)

## Responsive Breakpoints

- **768px**: 2-column grid, hide nav links, reduce padding
- Images always use `object-fit: cover` with `width: 100%`
- Items use `border-radius: 4px` (grid) or `16px` (feed)
